        <h4>Introduction:</h4>
        <p>In today’s increasingly digital world, cybersecurity is a fundamental skill everyone should be aware of. Whether you’re protecting personal data or ensuring the safety of your company’s systems, knowing the basics of cybersecurity is crucial in defending against cyberattacks.</p>

        <h4>Why is Cybersecurity Important?</h4>
        <p>Cybersecurity refers to the practice of protecting systems, networks, and data from digital attacks. With most aspects of our lives connected online, from banking to communication, safeguarding this information is critical. Cybersecurity helps protect sensitive data from unauthorized access, cyberattacks, and disruptions.</p>

        <h4>Basic Cybersecurity Practices for Beginners</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Use Strong Passwords: Always use a mix of letters, numbers, and symbols in your passwords to ensure they are hard to guess.</li>
          <li>Enable Two-Factor Authentication: This adds an additional layer of security to your online accounts, requiring two forms of verification.</li>
          <li>Keep Software Updated: Regular updates protect your devices from known vulnerabilities.</li>
          <li>Be Aware of Phishing Scams: Be cautious of suspicious emails and websites that try to trick you into revealing sensitive information.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Conclusion:</h4>
        <p>As digital threats continue to evolve, staying informed and practicing good cybersecurity hygiene is key to protecting yourself and your data. Whether you're just starting or looking to expand your knowledge, the basics of cybersecurity are the foundation for a secure digital presence.</p>
